---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "May 8, 2026";
const effectiveDate = "May 8, 2026";

const sections = [
  { id: "scope", title: "1. Scope" },
  { id: "controller", title: "2. Data controller" },
  { id: "data-we-collect", title: "3. Data we collect" },
  { id: "purposes", title: "4. How we use data" },
  { id: "third-parties", title: "5. Third-party services" },
  { id: "ads", title: "6. Advertising & ATT" },
  { id: "subscriptions", title: "7. Subscriptions" },
  { id: "retention", title: "8. Retention" },
  { id: "transfers", title: "9. International transfers" },
  { id: "rights", title: "10. Your rights" },
  { id: "children", title: "11. Children" },
  { id: "changes", title: "12. Changes" },
  { id: "contact", title: "13. Contact" },
];
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How NexUtility collects, uses, and protects data across our mobile apps and this website."
  lastUpdated={lastUpdated}
  effectiveDate={effectiveDate}
  sections={sections}
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>NexUtility</strong> (referred to as
    <strong>"NexUtility"</strong>, <strong>"we"</strong>, <strong>"us"</strong>,
    or <strong>"our"</strong>) collects, uses, and protects information when you
    visit this website or use any mobile application we publish on the Apple App
    Store or Google Play Store (collectively, the <strong>"Services"</strong>).
  </p>

  <p>
    We have written this policy in plain language and have included specific
    sections required by Apple App Tracking Transparency, Google Data Safety,
    the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), and the KVKK.
  </p>

  <h2 id="scope">1. Scope</h2>
  <p>
    This policy covers <code>nexutility.com</code> and any mobile or
    cross-platform application linking to it as their privacy policy URL.
    Individual apps may publish a per-app supplement under
    <a href="/apps">/apps/[slug]</a> if they collect additional data; in that
    case, the supplement applies in addition to this policy.
  </p>

  <h2 id="controller">2. Data controller</h2>
  <p>
    The data controller for the Services is NexUtility,
    <code>[Legal entity name]</code>, <code>[Registered address]</code>.
    Inquiries can be sent to
    <a href="mailto:privacy@nexutility.com">privacy@nexutility.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="data-we-collect">3. Data we collect</h2>
  <p>
    We aim to collect the minimum data needed to operate, secure, and improve
    the Services. The categories below are <em>potential</em> categories — any
    given app collects only the subset listed in its App Store / Play Store
    privacy nutrition label and per-app supplement.
  </p>

  <h3>3.1 Provided directly</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Account & contact data</strong> — only if you contact support or
      explicitly create an account: name, email, message contents.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>App content</strong> — anything you save inside an app (notes,
      preferences, files). Stored on your device unless the app explicitly
      offers a sync feature.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.2 Collected automatically</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Device & technical data</strong> — operating system version,
      device model, app version, language, crash reports, anonymized
      diagnostics.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Usage data</strong> — events such as feature opens or paywall
      views, used to understand which features are valuable. Stored
      pseudonymously and not linked to your real identity unless you sign in.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Identifiers</strong> — an app-instance identifier, and (with your
      permission on iOS) the IDFA. On Android we may use the Advertising ID
      where required for ad delivery, subject to your opt-out.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Approximate IP-based location</strong> — to localize content,
      currency, and to apply regional legal requirements. We do not collect GPS
      location unless an app explicitly asks you and you grant permission.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="purposes">4. How we use data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To deliver and maintain the Services you request.</li>
    <li>To process subscription purchases and entitlement checks.</li>
    <li>To detect, investigate, and prevent fraud, abuse, and security incidents.</li>
    <li>To debug crashes, fix bugs, and improve performance.</li>
    <li>To measure aggregate product usage and inform feature decisions.</li>
    <li>To serve advertising in apps where ads are part of the product.</li>
    <li>To comply with our legal obligations and respond to lawful requests.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="third-parties">5. Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    We rely on a small number of third-party processors. Each one has its own
    privacy policy, linked below.
  </p>

  <h3>5.1 Hosting & delivery</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Cloudflare</strong> — website hosting, CDN, and DDoS protection.
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Policy</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>5.2 Subscription management</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>RevenueCat</strong> — verifies App Store / Play Store receipts,
      manages subscription entitlements, and provides anonymized purchase
      analytics. RevenueCat receives the App Store / Play Store anonymous
      identifier and a pseudonymous app-instance ID.
      <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Policy</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>5.3 Advertising</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Google AdMob</strong> — serves ads in apps that include
      advertising. AdMob may use device identifiers (IDFA / Advertising ID),
      coarse location, and ad-interaction signals as described in the
      <a href="https://support.google.com/admob/answer/6128543" rel="noopener" target="_blank">AdMob Help Center</a>
      and Google's
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>.
      Personalized ads are only shown after we obtain consent where required by
      Apple's App Tracking Transparency or the IAB EU Transparency & Consent
      Framework.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>5.4 App stores</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Apple</strong> processes purchases, Family Sharing, and refund
      requests under
      <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Apple's Privacy Policy</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Google</strong> processes purchases and identity for Play
      services under
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="ads">6. Advertising & App Tracking Transparency</h2>
  <p>
    On iOS, we comply with Apple's App Tracking Transparency framework. Before
    any tracking that links your device to data collected by other companies'
    apps or websites for advertising, we will request your explicit permission.
    If you decline, you will still see ads in supported apps, but they will be
    non-personalized.
  </p>
  <p>
    On Android, you can reset or opt out of personalized advertising at any
    time from the system settings ("Privacy" → "Ads" → "Delete advertising ID"
    or "Opt out of Ads Personalization").
  </p>

  <h2 id="subscriptions">7. Subscriptions, restore & refunds</h2>
  <p>
    Some of our apps offer optional subscriptions. Subscriptions are billed
    through Apple or Google according to the price and period shown at
    purchase. Subscriptions auto-renew until cancelled at least 24 hours before
    the end of the current period. You can manage and cancel subscriptions in
    your App Store or Google Play account settings.
  </p>
  <p>
    Refunds are processed by Apple or Google according to their refund
    policies. We can help you locate the right form on
    <a href="/support">/support</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="retention">8. Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep diagnostic data and usage logs for up to 12 months. Subscription
    receipts are retained for as long as your subscription is active and for an
    additional period required by tax and accounting law, typically up to 10
    years. Support tickets are kept for up to 24 months after the last reply.
  </p>

  <h2 id="transfers">9. International transfers</h2>
  <p>
    Some of our processors are located outside your country (for example in the
    United States or the European Union). When personal data is transferred
    outside your country of residence, we rely on Standard Contractual Clauses
    or equivalent safeguards approved by the relevant data protection
    authority.
  </p>

  <h2 id="rights">10. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you have rights under GDPR, KVKK, the
    California Consumer Privacy Act, and similar laws. These typically include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The right to access a copy of your personal data.</li>
    <li>The right to rectify inaccurate data.</li>
    <li>The right to erasure ("right to be forgotten").</li>
    <li>The right to restrict or object to processing.</li>
    <li>The right to data portability.</li>
    <li>The right to withdraw consent at any time.</li>
    <li>The right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise any of these rights, email
    <a href="mailto:privacy@nexutility.com">privacy@nexutility.com</a>. We will
    respond within 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2 id="children">11. Children</h2>
  <p>
    Our Services are not directed to children under 13 (or the equivalent
    minimum age in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal
    data from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal
    data, please contact us and we will delete it.
  </p>

  <h2 id="changes">12. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will
    revise the "Last updated" date at the top. Material changes will be
    announced inside the affected app or via email to known contacts.
  </p>

  <h2 id="contact">13. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Privacy questions:
    <a href="mailto:privacy@nexutility.com">privacy@nexutility.com</a>
    <br />
    General support:
    <a href="mailto:support@nexutility.com">support@nexutility.com</a>
  </p>

  <p class="!mt-12 rounded-md border border-warning/30 bg-warning/5 p-4 text-sm text-fg-muted">
    <strong>Note for the team:</strong> This document is a working template.
    Replace bracketed values (legal entity name, registered address) before
    submitting any app for review and have it reviewed by counsel for the
    jurisdictions you ship to.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
